{{Quote|When Xim the Despot and his droid legions attempted to invade Hutt space, the great Kossak defeated them at Vontor and sent them fleeing for the Tion Hegemony.|[[Borga Besadii Diori]]|<ref name="JE">''[[The New Jedi Order: Agents of Chaos II: Jedi Eclipse]]''</ref>}}
'''Vontor''' was a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] located in the [[Si'Klaata Cluster/Legends|Si'Klaata Cluster]] within the boundaries of [[Hutt Space/Legends|Hutt Space]]. Vontor was a huge source of [[Kiirium/Legends|kiirium]].<ref name="Despotica">{{Hyperspace|url=fans/hyperspace/source/ximweek02/index.html|text=Xim Week: ''The Despotica'' (Part I)|int=Xim Week: The Despotica}}</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|It's a war-robot. Xim the Despot built a brigade of them to serve as his absolutely faithful royal guard. They were, at that time, the most formidable human-form fighting machines in the galaxy. This one's remains were recovered from the floating ruins of Xim's orbital fortress, possibly the only one that wasn't vaporized in the Third Battle of Vontor, Xim's final defeat.|[[Professor/Legends|Professor]] [[S. V. Skynx/Legends|S. V. Skynx]]|<ref name="HSatLL">''[[Han Solo and the Lost Legacy]]''</ref>}}
Before the founding of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], three battles between the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutts]] and the forces of [[Xim/Legends|Xim the Despot]] were fought here as part of the [[Xim Wars]]. The [[First Battle of Vontor|first]] [[Second Battle of Vontor|two]] ended in stalemate. In the [[Third Battle of Vontor|third]], [[25,100 BBY]], the Hutts under [[Kossak Inijic Ar'durv|Kossak]] surprised Xim with a horde of their newest allies—the [[Weequay/Legends|Weequays]], [[Vodran (species)/Legends|Vodrans]], [[Nikto/Legends|Nikto]], and [[Klatooinian/Legends|Klatooinians]]—and defeated Xim.<ref name="TEA" />

